<section xml:id="sec-calculus-in-polar-coordinates">
  <title>Calculus in polar coordinates</title>

  <objectives>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Find slopes of tangent lines to curves given in polar form.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Compute arc lengths using the polar arc length formula.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Determine areas of regions bounded by one or more polar curves.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </objectives>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Introduction goes here.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        Derivative:
        <me>
          \dv{y}{x} =\frac{\dd(r\sin\theta)}{\dd(r\cos\theta)}=\frac{r\cos\theta\dd{\theta}+\sin\theta\dd{r}}{-r\sin\theta\dd{\theta}+\cos\theta\dd{r}}=\frac{r\cos\theta+r'\sin\theta}{-r\sin\theta+r'\cos\theta}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Arc length:
        <me>
          s=\int_{\alpha}^{\beta} \sqrt{r^{2}+\qty(\dv{r}{\theta})^{2}}\dd{\theta}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Polar area bounded by one curve:
        <me>
          A=\frac{1}{2}\int_{\alpha}^{\beta} r^{2}\dd{\theta}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p>
        Polar area bounded by two curves:
        <me>
          A=\frac{1}{2}\int_{\alpha}^{\beta} (r\tsub{outer}^{2}-r\tsub{inner}^{2})\dd{\theta}
        </me>
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>
